- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper describes a system for data analysis and mining. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is relevant as the paper discusses social science concepts and applies them to the analysis of social networks. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch on issues of privacy and security in the context of analyzing social network data. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper describes a method for frequent itemset mining and data cube analysis.
